4. Customer Booking Experience Architecture

Booking Experience Model

AirportFaster must support a search-first booking experience.

Primary booking route:
Homepage / Airport page → Search → Service selection → Details → Checkout → Confirmation

⸻

5. Customer Flow 1 — Homepage to Booking

Flow Steps

Step 1: Customer lands on homepage

Customer sees:

* Search module
* Premium value proposition
* Trust indicators

Step 2: Customer searches airport

Inputs:

* Airport / city / country
* Service type optional
* Date
* Time
* Passenger count

Step 3: Search results display available services

Customer sees:

* Fast Track
* Meet & Greet
* Lounge Access
* Service cards
* Price indication
* Availability status

Step 4: Customer selects service

Customer enters booking flow.

Step 5: Customer fills service details

Required details:

* Passenger name
* Email
* Phone/WhatsApp
* Flight number
* Arrival/departure type
* Date/time
* Passenger count
* Special requests

Step 6: Customer reviews booking

Customer sees:

* Service summary
* Airport
* Date/time
* Passenger count
* Price
* Cancellation policy

Step 7: Customer pays

Payment is processed securely.

Step 8: Booking confirmation

Customer receives:

* Booking reference
* Email confirmation
* WhatsApp confirmation
* Manage booking link

Step 9: Operations workflow starts

Booking appears in admin dashboard.
Supplier assignment begins.

