11. Admin Flow 1 — Add New Airport

Purpose

Allow full admin control over airport expansion without developer intervention.

Flow Steps

Step 1: Admin opens Airports module

Admin clicks “Add Airport”.

Step 2: Admin enters airport basic information

Fields:

* Airport name
* IATA code
* ICAO code
* Country
* City
* Timezone
* Airport status
* Featured status

Step 3: Admin adds airport content

Fields:

* Short description
* Full description
* Arrival instructions
* Departure instructions
* Transit instructions
* Images

Step 4: Admin configures services

Admin selects available services:

* Fast Track
* Meet & Greet
* Lounge Access

For each service:

* Active/inactive
* Cut-off time
* Availability rules
* Price rules
* Supplier options

Step 5: Admin configures SEO

Fields:

* URL slug
* Meta title
* Meta description
* Focus keywords
* FAQs
* Schema content
* OG image
* Canonical URL

Step 6: Admin adds translations

Languages:

* English
* Arabic

Future:

* Turkish
* Russian
* French
* German

Step 7: Admin assigns suppliers

Admin maps supplier(s) to airport services.

Step 8: Admin previews airport page

Preview must show:

* Public page
* SEO snippet preview
* Mobile preview

Step 9: Admin publishes airport

After publishing:

* Airport appears on website
* Airport becomes searchable
* SEO page becomes live
* Services become bookable

