Document Review & Corrections (v1.1)

Reviewed 2026-05-14. Flows and page architecture preserved; the following corrections apply.

1. Canonical admin navigation. The admin dashboard navigation is: Overview, Bookings, Airports, Services, Suppliers, Customers, Operations, Incidents, Finance, Refunds, CMS / SEO, AI Engine (SEO & Translation review queues), Analytics, Notifications, Settings, Roles & Permissions. The list in section 9 is updated to include Refunds, AI Engine, and Roles & Permissions.

2. Checkout flow reflects merchant-of-record + charge-at-checkout. In Customer Flow 1, "Step 7: Customer pays" captures the full payment immediately via Stripe (DECISIONS.md D-006, D-007). The booking moves Pending Payment → Paid → Pending Supplier Assignment. If a supplier later cannot fulfil, the Refund flow (Admin Flow 7) is triggered.

3. AI review queues are MVP UX. Admin Flow 8 (CMS / SEO Publishing) is extended: AI-generated drafts (descriptions, metadata, FAQs, schema, summaries, guides) and AI translation drafts enter a review queue and follow Draft → Review → Edit → Approve → Publish. AI content never auto-publishes.

4. Pricing setup UX (Admin Flow 14). "Pricing source" options are confirmed as: fixed AirportFaster price OR supplier cost + markup, selectable per airport/service (D-008). "Future dynamic pricing" remains a non-MVP placeholder.

5. Roles. Seven roles including Analyst (read-only). Reflect in Settings → Roles & Permissions UX.

6. Booking status lifecycle in section 8 is confirmed correct and matches the System Architecture and Database Architecture documents.